Boil a full #kettle{}. Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel).

Pour the boiling water into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/2%tsp}. Add the potato chunks to the water and cook until you can easily slip a knife through, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2} (or use a #garlic press{}). Trim the @cucumber{1/2} (see ingredients for amount), then halve lengthways. Cut lengthways into roughly 1cm wide strips, then cut into 1cm pieces widthways.

Drain and rinse the @butter beans{1%carton} in a #sieve{}. Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{60%g}.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once hot, fry the @diced chorizo{90%g} until starting to brown, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Add the garlic and @North Indian style spice mix{1%sachet} and fry until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Stir in the @tomato passata{1%carton}, @vegetable stock paste{10%g}, butter beans and @water{50%ml}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Bring to a boil, then lower the heat and simmer until thickened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Meanwhile, in large #bowl{}, combine the @red wine vinegar{12%ml} and @sugar{1/2%tsp} for the dressing. Add the cucumber, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat.

Once the potatoes are cooked, drain in a #colander{} and return to the pan, off the heat.

Add a knob of @butter{} and a splash of milk (if you have any) and mash with a #potato masher{} until smooth.

Season with salt and pepper. Cover with a #lid{} to keep warm.

Once the sauce has thickened, stir through the @mango chutney{40%g} and @butter{20%g}. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed.

Add a splash of water if you feel it needs it. Remove from the heat.

Next, add the @olive oil{1%tbsp} for the dressing to the bowl with the cucumber.

Just before you're ready to serve, toss the @baby leaf mix{50%g} through the dressing.

Share the mash between your plates and top with the curried beans.

Sprinkle the cheese over the beans.

Serve with the salad alongside. Enjoy!